Annotation value management commands.

USAGE:
  scw annotations value <command>

AVAILABLE COMMANDS:
  create                  Add a value definition to a key.
  delete                  Delete a value definition. Fails if the value is currently bound to any resource.
  delete-all-matching-key Delete ALL values associated with a key. Fails if any of these values are currently bound to any resource.
  get                     Retrieve a specific value.
  list                    List all values for a key, sorted alphabetically by name.
  update                  Update name or description. Global update.

FLAGS:
  -h, --help                help for value
      --list-sub-commands   List all subcommands

GLOBAL FLAGS:
  -c, --config string    The path to the config file
  -D, --debug            Enable debug mode
  -o, --output string    Output format: json or human, see 'scw help output' for more info (default "human")
  -p, --profile string   The config profile to use

Use "scw annotations value [command] --help" for more information about a command.
